16
00:00:42,126 --> 00:00:44,296
These are the label samples the Design Team sent over.

17
00:00:44,766 --> 00:00:47,066
The drawing of a group of people...

18
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:49,266
is great at accentuating the name,

19
00:00:49,367 --> 00:00:50,405
but I think...

20
00:00:50,406 --> 00:00:52,975
It doesn't show the taste or flavour and strength...

21
00:00:52,976 --> 00:00:55,406
of the beer that we want to promote.

22
00:01:03,846 --> 00:01:04,857
(Posters)

23
00:01:06,856 --> 00:01:09,486
Shall we call it a day, then?

24
00:01:09,487 --> 00:01:10,487
Yes.

25
00:01:13,226 --> 00:01:15,267
- Bye. - See you.

26
00:01:17,326 --> 00:01:19,696
(Posters)

27
00:01:31,317 --> 00:01:32,317
(Min Ju)

28
00:01:34,317 --> 00:01:38,257
(Min Ju)

29
00:01:40,157 --> 00:01:42,856
Is something bothering Ms. Chae?

30
00:01:42,987 --> 00:01:44,797
Together went into mass production.

31
00:01:45,196 --> 00:01:46,757
She's worried the taste will shift.

32
00:01:50,297 --> 00:01:52,496
I heard about that term.

33
00:01:52,936 --> 00:01:55,166
What exactly does it mean when taste "shifts?"

34
00:01:56,537 --> 00:01:58,507
Even if the ingredients and recipe are the same,

35
00:01:58,707 --> 00:02:01,177
depending on the maturing, fermenting, temperature and things,

36
00:02:01,377 --> 00:02:03,146
unpredictable minute changes...

37
00:02:03,147 --> 00:02:04,715
can affect the beer's taste.

38
00:02:04,716 --> 00:02:05,776
Yes.

39
00:02:05,877 --> 00:02:08,686
Our first batch is 3,330,000 bottles.

40
00:02:09,017 --> 00:02:11,986
That means all 3,330,000 beers must taste the same.

41
00:02:11,987 --> 00:02:13,656
But something minute could change that.

42
00:02:13,816 --> 00:02:15,386
Industry people call that...

43
00:02:15,387 --> 00:02:17,226
a taste shift.

44
00:02:17,227 --> 00:02:19,326
I panic when I go from cooking one packet...

45
00:02:19,327 --> 00:02:20,957
of noodles to ten at once.

46
00:02:21,197 --> 00:02:22,827
Over 3.33 million beers...

47
00:02:26,496 --> 00:02:28,806
Mr. Yoon must be really stressed out too.

48
00:02:29,237 --> 00:02:32,006
- Is he okay? - That's why Ms. Chae's worried.

49
00:02:32,876 --> 00:02:34,536
(Fermented Liquor, Chapter 1: Beer)

50
00:02:44,447 --> 00:02:45,887
(Craftsman Bartender and Brewery Management)

51
00:02:55,227 --> 00:02:56,267
Hey.

52
00:02:58,267 --> 00:03:00,095
- You said you'd be working late. - Yes.

53
00:03:00,096 --> 00:03:01,096
What's up?

54
00:03:01,097 --> 00:03:03,767
I rushed over after sitting in meetings all day long.

55
00:03:04,906 --> 00:03:06,806
You must be busy with the release.

56
00:03:07,207 --> 00:03:08,406
You should get some rest.

57
00:03:09,107 --> 00:03:11,106
I'm here because I had a feeling our brewmaster...

58
00:03:11,107 --> 00:03:12,947
would be too worried to sleep.

59
00:03:15,186 --> 00:03:17,185
Seeing you wiped away my worries.

60
00:03:17,186 --> 00:03:18,617
- Did it? - Yes.

61
00:03:40,207 --> 00:03:41,207
Goodness.

62
00:03:41,208 --> 00:03:43,477
You're looking out for me when you must be busy?

63
00:03:45,077 --> 00:03:47,177
Looking out for the brewmaster...

64
00:03:47,846 --> 00:03:50,117
is part of my job as head of the team.

65
00:04:03,327 --> 00:04:04,797
It gets to you, doesn't it?

66
00:04:05,367 --> 00:04:06,397
It does.

67
00:04:06,936 --> 00:04:10,505
I've never produced this much beer in one go.

68
00:04:10,506 --> 00:04:11,875
In this field,

69
00:04:11,876 --> 00:04:14,077
a taste shift isn't rare.

70
00:04:14,806 --> 00:04:17,246
But that doesn't mean it's a defect.

71
00:04:17,677 --> 00:04:20,076
It's just a minute change in taste.

72
00:04:20,376 --> 00:04:23,847
But people who drink the same thing all the time...

73
00:04:24,386 --> 00:04:25,686
can tell right away.

74
00:04:27,056 --> 00:04:29,227
They go, "Hey, the beer tastes different."

75
00:04:30,987 --> 00:04:32,927
That's the scariest.

76
00:04:33,097 --> 00:04:34,227
It is.

77
00:04:35,266 --> 00:04:37,097
- Is there anything I can do? - What?

78
00:04:39,066 --> 00:04:40,167
Hang on.

79
00:04:43,136 --> 00:04:44,167
Hi, Beom.

80
00:04:45,777 --> 00:04:46,805
Really?

81
00:04:46,806 --> 00:04:49,347
Schedule a meeting tomorrow with the head of SCM.

82
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:52,677
Yes, sure. Thanks.

83
00:04:57,246 --> 00:05:00,357
Go home. You have work tomorrow.

84
00:05:01,456 --> 00:05:03,527
I can stay another hour.

85
00:05:05,556 --> 00:05:08,626
Then spend that extra hour on sleep.

86
00:05:10,826 --> 00:05:11,967
Get going.

87
00:05:13,636 --> 00:05:14,636
Get up.

88
00:05:18,277 --> 00:05:20,936
No, wait. I'll drive you.

89
00:05:21,177 --> 00:05:22,806
You can nap on the way.

90
00:05:23,777 --> 00:05:26,316
- You're too tired to drive. - I'm fine.

91
00:05:26,446 --> 00:05:28,286
We have a good recipe...

92
00:05:28,287 --> 00:05:29,717
and we won the contest.

93
00:05:30,146 --> 00:05:33,056
And the chairman's tasting went fabulously.

94
00:05:33,287 --> 00:05:34,857
Our beer is perfect.

95
00:05:36,027 --> 00:05:37,657
I got you worried for nothing.

96
00:05:37,956 --> 00:05:40,527
Don't say "nothing." Of course we should worry together.

97
00:05:40,727 --> 00:05:42,566
That's the name of our beer. Together.

98
00:05:44,597 --> 00:05:45,995
See you when the first batch is out.

99
00:05:45,996 --> 00:05:47,367
- Bye. - Bye.

100
00:05:50,967 --> 00:05:51,977
See you.

101
00:05:58,446 --> 00:06:03,087
(Brewing Love)

102
00:06:07,917 --> 00:06:09,157
Hello, sir.

103
00:06:09,587 --> 00:06:11,527
The first batch is being transported today.

104
00:06:11,657 --> 00:06:13,256
I was thinking about stopping by the factory to...

105
00:06:15,766 --> 00:06:18,066
What did you just say?

106
00:06:20,337 --> 00:06:22,206
Why can't the beer be transported today?

107
00:06:23,566 --> 00:06:24,837
What on earth are you saying?

108
00:06:26,576 --> 00:06:28,907
I'll come to you. I'll be right there.

109
00:06:35,446 --> 00:06:37,417
(Jisang Liquor)

110
00:06:42,886 --> 00:06:43,927
Min Ju.

111
00:06:47,056 --> 00:06:50,227
The first batch of products can't leave the factory today.

112
00:06:51,396 --> 00:06:53,337
- It can't happen. - Hold on.

113
00:06:55,407 --> 00:06:56,667
Were you the one who stepped on the brakes?

114
00:06:58,907 --> 00:07:00,436
What are you saying?

115
00:07:01,746 --> 00:07:03,576
They must leave the factory today...

116
00:07:03,746 --> 00:07:05,446
to be sent to direct-only stores across the country.

117
00:07:05,777 --> 00:07:07,476
What if we can't meet the launch deadline?

118
00:07:07,477 --> 00:07:08,547
Push the deadline back.

119
00:07:09,117 --> 00:07:11,246
I also have authority over the launch of Together.

120
00:07:12,456 --> 00:07:14,686
Yoon Min Ju, what's going on?

121
00:07:15,727 --> 00:07:18,956
This is our beer. We made it together.

122
00:07:21,927 --> 00:07:23,227
This batch of beer...

123
00:07:24,496 --> 00:07:26,037
will be dumped,

124
00:07:27,066 --> 00:07:28,097
Ms. Chae.

125
00:07:39,777 --> 00:07:41,076
Taste both of them.

126
00:07:56,227 --> 00:07:58,436
(Jisang Liquor)

127
00:08:04,566 --> 00:08:06,006
There's a subtle difference to the taste.

128
00:08:06,977 --> 00:08:08,176
Was there a taste shift?

129
00:08:08,177 --> 00:08:09,805
When we produced the first batch,

130
00:08:09,806 --> 00:08:11,276
we used a different fermenting tank.

131
00:08:11,277 --> 00:08:12,816
I think that affected the taste.

132
00:08:13,646 --> 00:08:15,245
I can't have it released in this state.

133
00:08:15,246 --> 00:08:16,445
Give me a little more time.

134
00:08:16,446 --> 00:08:18,455
I'll get the taste back on track. I can do it.

135
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:20,955
- No. We must ship it today. - Yong Ju.

136
00:08:20,956 --> 00:08:22,727
I'm speaking as the team leader.

137
00:08:23,256 --> 00:08:25,657
If we fail to release the first batch on time,

138
00:08:25,857 --> 00:08:27,657
our credibility will drop in no time.

139
00:08:27,826 --> 00:08:29,466
Don't you know how important credibility is?

140
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:30,967
Why are you thinking only about this one time?

141
00:08:31,396 --> 00:08:33,437
Consumers can even tell mineral water brands apart.

142
00:08:33,697 --> 00:08:35,436
If word gets out that it tastes different,

143
00:08:35,437 --> 00:08:37,005
they'll turn away from our brand.

144
00:08:37,006 --> 00:08:38,107
Then...

145
00:08:38,536 --> 00:08:40,477
what about the wholesalers waiting for our product?

146
00:08:40,676 --> 00:08:42,206
Who would trust us...

147
00:08:42,207 --> 00:08:44,607
and sell our product if we break our word from the start?

148
00:08:45,276 --> 00:08:48,486
A loss in credibility means a loss in sales.

149
00:08:48,487 --> 00:08:51,117
Who wants to drink a beer that tastes different each time?

150
00:08:51,886 --> 00:08:54,316
Once consumers turn away, we'll have to stop producing this.

151
00:08:54,317 --> 00:08:55,327
Min Ju.

152
00:08:56,457 --> 00:08:59,727
Do you know how much the product in the factory costs?

153
00:09:01,396 --> 00:09:02,626
It costs five million dollars.

154
00:09:03,526 --> 00:09:04,966
Five million dollars.

155
00:09:04,967 --> 00:09:07,796
If we halt production, we won't recover the five million...

156
00:09:08,296 --> 00:09:09,906
that went into the first batch,

157
00:09:10,107 --> 00:09:12,576
but we'll also lose the money we invested in developing it.

158
00:09:12,577 --> 00:09:14,006
That's a much bigger loss.

159
00:09:14,737 --> 00:09:16,706
You said you wanted our beer to do well.

160
00:09:16,707 --> 00:09:20,077
I'm doing this because I want our beer to do well.

161
00:09:21,847 --> 00:09:24,545
It's more important to keep our promise.

162
00:09:24,546 --> 00:09:26,915
It tasting perfect is more important.

163
00:09:26,916 --> 00:09:28,256
- Min Ju! - Yong Ju!

164
00:09:33,697 --> 00:09:34,996
Do you want our beer...

165
00:09:37,227 --> 00:09:39,536
to be a quick hit before it disappears?

166
00:09:43,937 --> 00:09:45,107
Go home.

167
00:09:46,807 --> 00:09:49,706
The directors will have heard about it by now.

168
00:09:49,707 --> 00:09:50,906
I must report to them.

169
00:09:52,016 --> 00:09:53,077
Yong Ju.

170
00:09:53,746 --> 00:09:55,046
We must stop it now.

171
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:57,087
This is our last chance.

172
00:09:57,516 --> 00:09:58,816
We identified the problem first...

173
00:09:58,817 --> 00:10:00,587
and can fix it so why won't you?

174
00:10:01,827 --> 00:10:04,827
It will come back at us as a much bigger problem.

175
00:10:08,197 --> 00:10:10,996
No company can accept this.

176
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:13,867
I work at Jisang Liquor...

177
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:16,937
and have a duty to follow their decision.

178
00:10:18,807 --> 00:10:20,136
Don't you see where I stand?

179
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,016
I'd like you to leave everything to us...

180
00:10:28,786 --> 00:10:30,317
from here on out.

181
00:10:49,067 --> 00:10:50,467
(Jisang Liquor)

182
00:11:03,016 --> 00:11:04,447
(Jisang Liquor)

183
00:11:05,357 --> 00:11:08,087
It's a precious beer we made together,

184
00:11:08,526 --> 00:11:10,187
so I'll make sure it's a hit.

185
00:11:11,026 --> 00:11:13,957
That being said, you'll properly see me do my work.

186
00:11:14,597 --> 00:11:16,626
I've been eyeing you from the moment we met.

187
00:11:25,107 --> 00:11:28,136
(Jisang Liquor)

188
00:11:34,016 --> 00:11:38,016
Do you want our beer to be a quick hit before it disappears?

189
00:11:50,197 --> 00:11:51,697
Are you kidding me?

190
00:11:52,536 --> 00:11:53,837
Why can't you release it?

191
00:11:54,097 --> 00:11:56,337
You used to work in sales!

192
00:11:56,837 --> 00:11:58,367
Don't you fear the sellers?

193
00:12:01,406 --> 00:12:05,107
(Marketing Director Na Tae Jo)

194
00:12:09,217 --> 00:12:10,416
I'm sorry, sir.

195
00:12:11,087 --> 00:12:12,156
But...

196
00:12:13,256 --> 00:12:14,916
now that I know it tastes different,

197
00:12:15,487 --> 00:12:17,426
it's only right to correct it before release.

198
00:12:18,357 --> 00:12:21,155
I'll apologize in person to each wholesaler...

199
00:12:21,156 --> 00:12:23,396
and ask for more time.

200
00:12:24,327 --> 00:12:25,396
Can't I do that?

201
00:12:27,697 --> 00:12:29,837
Are you out of your mind? Is this a joke?

202
00:12:30,006 --> 00:12:31,067
Sir.

203
00:12:32,136 --> 00:12:35,607
I know very well how nonsensical this is.

204
00:12:36,207 --> 00:12:37,207
But...

205
00:12:38,406 --> 00:12:39,946
it's also a fact that...

206
00:12:39,947 --> 00:12:42,187
a beer that tastes wrong doesn't last long.

207
00:12:42,447 --> 00:12:44,817
All the classic beers that the public still loves...

208
00:12:44,947 --> 00:12:47,216
tasted exactly the same until they took over...

209
00:12:47,217 --> 00:12:48,987
five percent of the market.

210
00:12:49,357 --> 00:12:51,926
Five percent of the market is worth 200 million dollars.

211
00:12:52,626 --> 00:12:56,026
That's the kind of beer Mr. Yoon wanted to make.

212
00:12:56,367 --> 00:12:58,295
This will profit us in the long run.

213
00:12:58,296 --> 00:13:01,197
That means throwing away five million dollars!

214
00:13:01,597 --> 00:13:03,967
Why would you even talk about classics lasting long?

215
00:13:05,676 --> 00:13:07,136
What are you saying?

216
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:10,246
How would the customers know it tastes different?

217
00:13:10,376 --> 00:13:11,675
No one will know!

218
00:13:11,676 --> 00:13:13,176
We know.

219
00:13:15,987 --> 00:13:17,087
You lot...

220
00:13:18,416 --> 00:13:19,856
You lost your minds...

221
00:13:19,857 --> 00:13:21,957
because the chairman has your backs.

222
00:13:22,656 --> 00:13:25,625
You seem to think you actually have the right to make decisions...

223
00:13:25,626 --> 00:13:27,827
because the chairman said so!

224
00:13:28,967 --> 00:13:30,697
Don't go too far...

225
00:13:31,937 --> 00:13:33,367
across the line.

226
00:13:35,097 --> 00:13:36,107
Get out.

227
00:13:37,536 --> 00:13:38,536
Get out!

228
00:13:57,156 --> 00:13:58,187
My gosh.

229
00:14:04,827 --> 00:14:06,237
You're the factory manager.

230
00:14:08,136 --> 00:14:09,307
What are you doing?

231
00:14:11,166 --> 00:14:13,737
Why would you listen to such nonsense?

232
00:14:14,077 --> 00:14:16,175
Who cares if it tastes a bit different?

233
00:14:16,176 --> 00:14:17,376
That's nothing!

234
00:14:18,046 --> 00:14:19,516
Ship the beer right away.

235
00:14:20,176 --> 00:14:22,117
Right now.

236
00:14:24,617 --> 00:14:25,687
What did he say?

237
00:14:25,987 --> 00:14:27,386
No, of course.

238
00:14:27,557 --> 00:14:29,025
It's hard for a company...

239
00:14:29,026 --> 00:14:30,625
to dump a batch for tasting off.

240
00:14:30,626 --> 00:14:32,796
Still, we can't just ship it out.

241
00:14:33,256 --> 00:14:34,796
I don't know what's right.

242
00:14:35,156 --> 00:14:38,097
I can understand and accept both positions.

243
00:14:38,626 --> 00:14:39,796
He's pretty firm.

244
00:14:40,097 --> 00:14:41,866
The situation isn't ideal,

245
00:14:41,867 --> 00:14:43,535
but if we release as planned today,

246
00:14:43,536 --> 00:14:45,505
we must set a distribution plan for the factory...

247
00:14:45,506 --> 00:14:47,036
and direct-only stores with the SCM Team.

248
00:14:49,146 --> 00:14:50,176
Yes.

249
00:14:51,146 --> 00:14:53,676
I have to talk to Mr. Yoon.

250
00:14:54,416 --> 00:14:56,145
Start the meeting without me.

251
00:14:56,146 --> 00:14:57,487
I need to make a call.

252
00:14:58,146 --> 00:14:59,256
Shall we go?

253
00:15:11,227 --> 00:15:12,597
It tastes wrong?

254
00:15:13,097 --> 00:15:15,506
(Planning Team Director Yeom Jang Goon)

255
00:15:16,766 --> 00:15:17,837
Hello.

256
00:15:19,607 --> 00:15:21,876
Have you heard, sir?

257
00:15:23,646 --> 00:15:25,876
Of course they must go ahead. It's too big a loss.

258
00:15:27,516 --> 00:15:30,847
If it were not just about a slight change in the taste...

259
00:15:31,016 --> 00:15:33,886
but about cloudy beer or yeast floating about,

260
00:15:34,057 --> 00:15:36,587
that would be scrapped for being a defect.

261
00:15:37,286 --> 00:15:38,357
It's a shame.

262
00:15:40,697 --> 00:15:43,097
Did I say something wrong?

263
00:15:43,266 --> 00:15:44,327
No.

264
00:15:45,227 --> 00:15:47,636
- You can go. - Yes, sir.

265
00:15:55,876 --> 00:15:57,006
This is how far you should go.

266
00:15:57,676 --> 00:15:58,947
If you continue on this path,

267
00:15:59,516 --> 00:16:01,347
you'll only be ruining yourself.

268
00:16:11,457 --> 00:16:12,496
I'll ruin myself?

269
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:15,026
We'll see who hits...

270
00:16:16,666 --> 00:16:17,766
rock bottom first.

271
00:16:28,847 --> 00:16:35,347
(Min Ju)

272
00:16:44,126 --> 00:16:46,526
I thought about it again and you were right.

273
00:16:47,097 --> 00:16:50,467
We're in charge of making it and we realized it tasted different.

274
00:16:50,996 --> 00:16:52,496
