00:51:21,037 --> 00:51:23,597
Director Yeom never gives me any important work.

817
00:51:24,336 --> 00:51:25,367
He's telling the truth.

818
00:51:26,336 --> 00:51:27,977
We appreciate your candour.

819
00:51:36,417 --> 00:51:38,086
(Planning Team Director Yeom Jang Goon)

820
00:51:42,316 --> 00:51:44,687
(Jisang Liquor)

821
00:51:48,097 --> 00:51:49,496
How do you know his password?

822
00:51:49,497 --> 00:51:51,096
It's the company's start date.

823
00:51:51,097 --> 00:51:52,366
Because he doesn't trust others,

824
00:51:52,367 --> 00:51:53,996
he writes important documents himself.

825
00:51:53,997 --> 00:51:56,135
Since he never knows when he'll need them,

826
00:51:56,136 --> 00:51:58,066
he always stores backup files.

827
00:52:00,836 --> 00:52:01,877
I found it.

828
00:52:03,406 --> 00:52:04,476
(Viral press release by Anon)

829
00:52:04,477 --> 00:52:05,706
(Jisang Liquor's Together Has Quality Issues)

830
00:52:05,707 --> 00:52:06,846
(Consumers complain about inconsistency with beer.)

831
00:52:06,847 --> 00:52:07,847
(Experts question issues during production.)

832
00:52:08,477 --> 00:52:09,816
How dare he mess with Together?

833
00:52:10,877 --> 00:52:13,586
When the TF Team put in all that work?

834
00:52:14,316 --> 00:52:15,886
There's a line one shouldn't cross.

835
00:52:16,687 --> 00:52:18,057
Ms. Beautiful Bang,

836
00:52:18,756 --> 00:52:20,787
I see you care greatly about Together.

837
00:52:22,656 --> 00:52:25,397
The chairman must've heard the news by now.

838
00:52:25,526 --> 00:52:26,997
If we can't explain this,

839
00:52:28,937 --> 00:52:30,597
we will all lose our jobs.

840
00:52:30,836 --> 00:52:32,366
Forget everything else...

841
00:52:32,367 --> 00:52:34,006
and prioritize the search of this traitor.

842
00:52:34,136 --> 00:52:35,635
Find out who it is, press charges,

843
00:52:35,636 --> 00:52:37,576
and receive an apology...

844
00:52:37,577 --> 00:52:39,307
stating that the article was released out of spite.

845
00:52:39,676 --> 00:52:41,776
Only that can save our skin.

846
00:52:51,986 --> 00:52:53,386
The traitor is right here.

847
00:52:55,397 --> 00:52:56,397
It's Director Yeom.

848
00:52:58,827 --> 00:53:01,795
Bang Ah Reum, what is the meaning of this?

849
00:53:01,796 --> 00:53:04,367
I know you a lot better...

850
00:53:04,667 --> 00:53:06,466
than you think.

851
00:53:06,566 --> 00:53:08,876
You were the only one at this company...

852
00:53:08,877 --> 00:53:11,046
that I was inspired to be like.

853
00:53:11,807 --> 00:53:14,775
However, I'm afraid he's no longer around.

854
00:53:14,776 --> 00:53:15,846
(Viral press release by Anon)

855
00:53:15,847 --> 00:53:16,847
(Jisang Liquor's Together Has Quality Issues)

856
00:53:16,847 --> 00:53:17,847
(Consumers complain about inconsistency with beer.)

857
00:53:23,787 --> 00:53:26,925
I have been reporting back to Mr. Yeom of the Planning Team...

858
00:53:26,926 --> 00:53:29,496
about the new beer being developed by the TF Team.

859
00:53:29,497 --> 00:53:30,755
With the information I gave him,

860
00:53:30,756 --> 00:53:33,026
he's been trying to sabotage its launch.

861
00:53:33,196 --> 00:53:34,835
For having a negative impact...

862
00:53:34,836 --> 00:53:36,296
on the company's future and its financial situation,

863
00:53:36,997 --> 00:53:38,906
- I will gladly be punished. - Sir.

864
00:53:39,537 --> 00:53:42,306
I was already aware of Ms. Bang's situation...

865
00:53:42,307 --> 00:53:44,275
and gave her a strict warning.

866
00:53:44,276 --> 00:53:46,576
Since then, she has been nothing but loyal...

867
00:53:46,577 --> 00:53:48,117
to the team and the project.

868
00:53:52,517 --> 00:53:53,747
I hear you.

869
00:53:57,486 --> 00:54:00,886
Director Yeom, can I expect your letter of resignation?

870
00:54:01,397 --> 00:54:03,727
Or should I deal with it in my own way?

871
00:54:18,707 --> 00:54:20,176
This is all your fault!

872
00:54:21,247 --> 00:54:23,616
This wouldn't have happened to me...

873
00:54:23,617 --> 00:54:25,417
if the chairman hadn't brought you along.

874
00:54:25,687 --> 00:54:27,716
Why must I leave this company? Why?

875
00:54:30,187 --> 00:54:31,287
Sir.

876
00:54:51,606 --> 00:54:52,647
Are you all right?

877
00:54:53,377 --> 00:54:54,406
Yes.

878
00:55:03,417 --> 00:55:06,486
I've always been the first to be at work and the last to leave.

879
00:55:06,926 --> 00:55:09,196
While others drank their way to the top,

880
00:55:09,827 --> 00:55:11,295
I climbed the ranks...

881
00:55:11,296 --> 00:55:12,727
by planning the budget and analysing our strategies.

882
00:55:14,327 --> 00:55:16,796
After all the work I did to be in this position?

883
00:55:18,807 --> 00:55:19,867
Who is it?

884
00:55:23,406 --> 00:55:24,977
How dare you enter this office?

885
00:55:33,716 --> 00:55:35,156
(Planning Team Director Yeom Jang Goon)

886
00:55:38,327 --> 00:55:39,356
I know...

887
00:55:40,327 --> 00:55:43,057
how hard you had to work to sit in this office.

888
00:55:43,926 --> 00:55:45,227
Your eyes say it all.

889
00:55:46,966 --> 00:55:49,636
I also know how much you love Jisang Liquor.

890
00:55:49,796 --> 00:55:52,136
- So why must I get fired? - Exactly.

891
00:55:52,636 --> 00:55:55,207
- Who do you think is at fault? - That's...

892
00:55:58,307 --> 00:56:00,477
We all want what's best for ourselves.

893
00:56:01,577 --> 00:56:03,215
To be more successful than others.

894
00:56:03,216 --> 00:56:05,617
We all desire to reach the top!

895
00:56:07,216 --> 00:56:08,617
That's all I wanted as well.

896
00:56:09,486 --> 00:56:11,386
So I worked day and night.

897
00:56:12,986 --> 00:56:14,026
This is unfair.

898
00:56:14,156 --> 00:56:15,726
Not everyone does the unthinkable...

899
00:56:15,727 --> 00:56:18,127
just because they think they've been treated unfairly.

900
00:56:19,497 --> 00:56:22,466
Take a look at where you ended up.

901
00:56:25,236 --> 00:56:27,005
Is there a single person...

902
00:56:27,006 --> 00:56:28,977
who understands why you did what you did?

903
00:56:29,136 --> 00:56:30,807
Who's there beside you?

904
00:56:32,847 --> 00:56:34,406
As if that's important.

905
00:56:35,046 --> 00:56:36,877
There was a time when I thought like you.

906
00:56:37,917 --> 00:56:40,215
I only cared about being satisfied in my own bubble...

907
00:56:40,216 --> 00:56:41,787
and told myself I didn't need others, but...

908
00:56:44,017 --> 00:56:45,287
I couldn't have been more wrong.

909
00:56:46,886 --> 00:56:48,656
I needed at least one person...

910
00:56:50,127 --> 00:56:51,866
to see me for who I am.

911
00:56:51,867 --> 00:56:52,997
Do you know why?

912
00:56:54,227 --> 00:56:55,397
Because that one person...

913
00:56:56,196 --> 00:56:58,207
proves that I lived my life well,

914
00:56:59,906 --> 00:57:01,167
and furthermore,

915
00:57:03,176 --> 00:57:04,747
makes me be more of myself.

916
00:57:06,877 --> 00:57:09,316
If you haven't even tried to find that one person,

917
00:57:10,776 --> 00:57:12,386
apologize to yourself.

918
00:57:13,546 --> 00:57:15,187
As if you know anything.

919
00:57:15,716 --> 00:57:17,687
I didn't come here to patronize you...

920
00:57:18,627 --> 00:57:20,086
or offer words of comfort.

921
00:57:20,727 --> 00:57:25,196
I only came here because I knew I'd regret not saying this to you.

922
00:57:47,316 --> 00:57:49,556
We will recall every bottle manufactured...

923
00:57:49,557 --> 00:57:52,227
and offer refunds to consumers who have already bought any.

924
00:57:52,586 --> 00:57:55,195
Mr. Yoon, in the meantime, you will prepare for its relaunch.

925
00:57:55,196 --> 00:57:56,456
As for me, I'm off to deal...

926
00:57:56,457 --> 00:57:58,926
with the scoundrel at Baekmok Liquor.

927
00:57:59,267 --> 00:58:02,497
Those who spread false rumours and write malicious comments online...

928
00:58:02,836 --> 00:58:03,867
should be taught a lesson.

929
00:58:04,566 --> 00:58:05,636
Then...

930
00:58:07,066 --> 00:58:08,106
All right.

931
00:58:08,776 --> 00:58:09,836
Hold on.

932
00:58:10,276 --> 00:58:12,976
Should any problems arise, call me instantly...

933
00:58:12,977 --> 00:58:16,347
Ms. Chae, don't burden yourself with every task.

934
00:58:16,676 --> 00:58:19,146
Yong Ju, let us carry the burden with you.

935
00:58:19,147 --> 00:58:20,886
We're a team, aren't we?

936
00:58:21,086 --> 00:58:23,386
Exactly. We're a united team.

937
00:58:24,656 --> 00:58:26,727
What do you say? How about we wish us luck?

938
00:58:30,656 --> 00:58:31,727
Sure.

939
00:58:33,097 --> 00:58:34,466
What...

940
00:58:35,466 --> 00:58:37,796
- We still can't get it right. - Just get moving.

941
00:58:40,437 --> 00:58:42,336
Let's get it right the next time.

942
00:58:42,776 --> 00:58:44,306
- Okay? - We should raise our hands, right?

943
00:58:44,307 --> 00:58:45,675
We'll decide on that some other time.

944
00:58:45,676 --> 00:58:47,476
- Go on. I wish you luck. - Good luck.

945
00:58:47,477 --> 00:58:48,746
- I'll see you later. - I wish you luck.

946
00:58:48,747 --> 00:58:50,347
- See you later. - I'll get going.

947
00:58:50,917 --> 00:58:51,946
See you.

948
00:58:52,187 --> 00:58:53,386
- Good luck. - Right.

949
00:58:54,187 --> 00:58:55,216
I wish you luck too.

950
00:59:22,946 --> 00:59:25,086
(Jisang Liquor)

951
00:59:36,296 --> 00:59:38,597
(Jisang Liquor)

952
00:59:43,466 --> 00:59:45,606
- Want to join me for coffee? - I'm good.

953
01:00:19,636 --> 01:00:20,636
(Jisang Liquor)

954
01:00:20,637 --> 01:00:22,577
Sir, a glass of soju seems to be in order.

955
01:00:23,077 --> 01:00:25,546
Gosh, your shoulders. They couldn't be stiffer.

956
01:00:26,446 --> 01:00:29,046
- This calls for a manual massage. - I hear you.

957
01:00:34,986 --> 01:00:36,386
Would it kill him to join us?

958
01:01:02,276 --> 01:01:03,417
Mr. Park.

959
01:01:04,147 --> 01:01:06,117
The company chat room is blowing up.

960
01:01:06,216 --> 01:01:08,986
The director of the Planning Team got the boot.

961
01:01:09,417 --> 01:01:10,957
Sure, we should meet up right away.

962
01:01:11,756 --> 01:01:12,886
I'm leaving the office as we speak.

963
01:01:16,097 --> 01:01:19,097
Exactly. Talk about the unexpected.

964
01:01:19,497 --> 01:01:20,566
I'll be right out.

965
01:01:29,136 --> 01:01:30,477
Not a single person...

966
01:01:32,776 --> 01:01:34,377
has called.

967
01:01:54,367 --> 01:01:56,897
(Planning Team Director Yeom Jang Goon)

968
01:02:04,336 --> 01:02:09,546
(Planning Team Director Yeom Jang Goon)

969
01:02:26,127 --> 01:02:29,536
(Planning Team Director Yeom Jang Goon)

970
01:02:29,537 --> 01:02:34,236
(Letter of Resignation)

971
01:02:39,377 --> 01:02:42,617
Some things in this world can be messed with...

972
01:02:43,077 --> 01:02:45,946
while some things in this world are sacred.

973
01:02:46,886 --> 01:02:50,787
Together should've been off-limits from beginning to end.

974
01:02:51,017 --> 01:02:52,086
That's right.

975
01:02:52,957 --> 01:02:54,687
What you did was wrong.

976
01:03:28,926 --> 01:03:31,767
(Brewing Love)

977
01:03:32,426 --> 01:03:34,796
I know it was rough, Yong Ju.

978
01:03:34,926 --> 01:03:37,897
You did great, Chae Yong Ju.

979
01:03:38,437 --> 01:03:40,335
- Oh Chan Ran? - My name at birth.

980
01:03:40,336 --> 01:03:42,077
Only my family remembers it.

981
01:03:42,276 --> 01:03:45,706
It's about time you dealt with the closing of the Busan office.

982
01:03:45,707 --> 01:03:47,206
You're coming too, right?

983
01:03:47,207 --> 01:03:48,876
Absolutely not.

984
01:03:48,877 --> 01:03:52,085
It's okay. Do whatever it is you want now.

985
01:03:52,086 --> 01:03:55,517
Not being certain of something is also who you are.

986
01:03:55,716 --> 01:03:58,886
And I even love the indecisive Chae Yong Ju.
